{"kanda":6,"sarga":35,"description":"","verses":[{"v":1,"dev":"तेनशङ्खविमिश्रेणभेरीशब्देनराघवः ।उपयातिमहाबाहूरामःपरपुरञ्जयः","trans":"The mighty armed Rama, the conqueror of enemy cities, Raghava marched forth with the noise of the blowing of conches and the sounds of drums.","words":[{"d":"महाबाहुः","m":"mighty armed"},{"d":"परपुरञ्जयः","m":"conqueror of enemy cities"},{"d":"रामः","m":"Rama"},{"d":"शङ्खविमित्रेण","m":"blowing of conches"},{"d":"राघवः","m":"Raghava"},{"d":"भेरीशब्देन","m":"by the noise of drums"},{"d":"उपयाति","m":"marched forth."}]},{"v":2,"dev":"तंनिनादंनिशम्याथरावणोराक्षसेश्वरः ।मुहूर्तंध्यानमास्थायसचिवानभ्युदैक्षत","trans":"Ravana, the Lord of Rakshasas, looked at his ministers on hearing the sounds and reflecting for a moment.","words":[{"d":"अथ","m":"and then"},{"d":"राक्षसेश्वरः","m":"Lord of Rakshasas"},{"d":"रावणः","m":"Ravana"},{"d":"तम्","m":"that"},{"d":"निनादम्","m":"sound"},{"d":"निशम्य","m":"hearing"},{"d":"मुहूर्तम्","m":"for a moment"},{"d":"ध्यानम्","m":"reflecting"},{"d":"आस्थाय","m":"considering"},{"d":"सचिवान्","m":"ministers"},{"d":"अभ्युदैक्षत","m":"looked at."}]},{"v":3,"dev":"अथतान्सचिवांस्तत्रसर्वानाभाष्यरावणः ।सभांसन्नादयन् सर्वामित्युवाचमहाबलः जगत्सन्तापन्क्रूरोगर्हयन्राक्षसेश्वरः ।","trans":"Thereafter the mighty Lord of Rakshasas, a cruel one, a scourge of the world addressed the assembly of his ministers and spoke abusing them.","words":[{"d":"अथ","m":"and then"},{"d":"महाबलः","m":"very strong"},{"d":"जगत्सन्तापनः","m":"scourge of the world"},{"d":"क्रूरः","m":"cruel"},{"d":"राक्षसेश्वरः","m":"Lord of Rakshasas"},{"d":"रावणः","m":"Ravana"},{"d":"सर्वान्","m":"to all"},{"d":"सचिवान्","m":"companions"},{"d":"आभाष्य","m":"addressed"},{"d":"सर्वाम्","m":"every one"},{"d":"सभाम्","m":"entire assembly"},{"d":"संवादयन्","m":"speaking"},{"d":"गर्हयन्","m":"abused"},{"d":"इति","m":"this"},{"d":"उवाच","m":"said."}]},{"v":4,"dev":"तरणंसागरस्यापिविक्रमंबलसञ्जियम् यदुक्तवन्तोरामस्यभवन्तस्तन्मयाश्रुतम् ।","trans":"\"You have told me about the valour of Hanuman the messenger of Rama and his prowess in crossing the ocean which I heard just now.\"","words":[{"d":"भवन्तः","m":"time being"},{"d":"रामस्य","m":"Rama's"},{"d":"यत्","m":"that Hanuman"},{"d":"अस्यसागरस्य","m":"that ocean"},{"d":"तरणम्","m":"crossing"},{"d":"विक्रमम्","m":"valour"},{"d":"बलसञ्जियम्","m":"prowess"},{"d":"उक्तवन्तः","m":"have told"},{"d":"तत्","m":"all that"},{"d":"मया","m":"by me"},{"d":"श्रुतम्","m":"heard."}]},{"v":5,"dev":"भवतश्चाप्यहंवेमदियुद्धेसत्यपराक्रमान् तूषिकानीक्षतोऽन्योन्यंविदित्वारामविक्रमम् ।","trans":"\"Even though you are truly valorous in war, on knowing Rama's prowess, you are standing mute looking at each other. I know that.\"","words":[{"d":"द्युद्धे","m":"in war"},{"d":"सत्यपराक्रमान्","m":"of truthful valour"},{"d":"रामविक्रमम्","m":"Rama's prowess"},{"d":"विदित्वा","m":"knowing"},{"d":"तूषिकान्","m":"stand mute"},{"d":"अन्योन्यम्","m":"each other"},{"d":"ईक्षतः","m":"looking at"},{"d":"भवतश्चापि","m":"I know you too"},{"d":"अहम्","m":"I"},{"d":"वेमदि","m":"know."}]},{"v":6,"dev":"ततस्तुसुमहाप्राज्ञोमाल्यवान्नामराक्षसः रावणस्यवचश्श्रुत्वामातुःपैतामहोऽब्रवीत् ।","trans":"Then, Malyavan the maternal grandfather of Ravana, a very wise Rakshasa indeed said this on hearing Ravana's statement.","words":[{"d":"ततः","m":"then"},{"d":"सुमहाप्राज्ञः","m":"very wise"},{"d":"मातुः","m":"maternal"},{"d":"माल्यवान्","m":"Malyavan नाम by name"},{"d":"राक्षरः","m":"Rakshasa"},{"d":"रावणस्य","m":"Ravana's"},{"d":"वचः","m":"conversation"},{"d":"श्रुत्वा","m":"hearing"},{"d":"पैतामहः","m":"grandfather"},{"d":"अब्रवीत्","m":"said."}]},{"v":7,"dev":"विद्यास्वभिविनीतोयोराजाराजन्नयानुगः सशास्तिचिरमैश्वर्यमरींश्चकुरुतेवशे ।","trans":"\"O king! Whoever is well versed in all the fourteen sciences and is a follower of justice, he alone wins over enemies and rules the kingdom for long.\"","words":[{"d":"राजन्","m":"O King"},{"d":"यः","m":"whoever"},{"d":"राजा","m":"king"},{"d":"विद्यासु","m":"all the fourteen sciences"},{"d":"अभिविनीतः","m":"path of justice"},{"d":"सः","m":"he"},{"d":"चिरम्","m":"for long"},{"d":"ऐश्वर्यम्","m":"sovereignty"},{"d":"शास्ति","m":"ruler"},{"d":"अरींश्च","m":"enemies"},{"d":"वशे","m":"win over"},{"d":"कुरुते","m":"enjoys"}]},{"v":8,"dev":"सन्दधानोहिकालेनविगृह्णंश्चारिभिस्सह स्वपक्षवर्थनंकुर्वन्महदैश्वर्यमश्नुते ।","trans":"\"Continuing to act in that way in course of time a king who encounters his enemies and expands his own side, enjoys great sovereignty.\"","words":[{"d":"कालेन","m":"at that time"},{"d":"अरिभिः","m":"enemies"},{"d":"सन्दधानः","m":"encountering"},{"d":"विगृह्णान्","m":"expanding"},{"d":"स्वपक्ष","m":"one's own side"},{"d":"वर्थनम्","m":"acting"},{"d":"कुर्वन्","m":"doing"},{"d":"महत्","m":"great"},{"d":"ऐश्वर्यम्","m":"sovereignty"},{"d":"अश्नुते","m":"enjoys."}]},{"v":9,"dev":"हीयमानेनकर्तव्योराज्ञासन्धिस्समेवच नशत्रुमवमन्येतज्यायान्कुर्वीतविग्रहम् ।","trans":"\"When a king is losing strength, he should join hand s with the enemy who is equal to him. He should not disrespect the enemy but quit his hostility and join him (if the enemy is more powerful).\"","words":[{"d":"हीयमानेन","m":"when losing strength"},{"d":"समेवच","m":"with equal"},{"d":"राज्ञा","m":"with king"},{"d":"सन्धिः","m":"join"},{"d":"कर्तव्यः","m":"duty"},{"d":"शत्रुम्","m":"with enemy"},{"d":"नअवमन्येत","m":"not disrespecting"},{"d":"ज्यायान्","m":"quitting"},{"d":"विग्रहम्","m":"hostility"},{"d":"कुर्वीत","m":"do."}]},{"v":10,"dev":"तन्मह्यंरोचतेसन्धिस्सहरामेणरावण यदर्थमभियुक्ता: स्मसीतातस्मैप्रदीयताम् ।","trans":"\"O Ravana! Joining with that Rama is agreeable to me. Let that Sita for whose sake you have been attacked be restored to him.\"","words":[{"d":"रावण","m":"Ravana"},{"d":"तत्","m":"that"},{"d":"रामेणसह","m":"with Rama"},{"d":"सन्धिः","m":"join"},{"d":"मह्यम्","m":"for us"},{"d":"रोचते","m":"agreeable"},{"d":"यदर्थम्","m":"for which"},{"d":"अभियुक्ता:","m":"favourable"},{"d":"स्मसीता","m":"Sita"},{"d":"तस्मै","m":"to him"},{"d":"प्रतीयताम्","m":"restore to him."}]},{"v":11,"dev":"यस्यदेवर्षयस्सर्वेगन्धर्वाश्चजयैषिणः विरोथंमागमस्तेनसन्धिस्तेतेनरोचताम् ।","trans":"All the celestial sages and Gandharvas are wishing him victory. Therefore, do not have enmity. Making an alliance with him is desirable for you.","words":[{"d":"सर्वे","m":"all"},{"d":"देवर्षय:","m":"celestial sages गन्धर्वाश्च Gandharvas"},{"d":"यस्य","m":"their"},{"d":"जयैषिणः","m":"wishing victory"},{"d":"तेन","m":"therefore"},{"d":"विरोधम्","m":"enmity"},{"d":"मागमः","m":"do not"},{"d":"ते","m":"to you"},{"d":"तेन","m":"therefore"},{"d":"सन्धिः","m":"alliance"},{"d":"रोचताम्","m":"desirable."}]},{"v":12,"dev":"असृजद्भगवान्पक्षौद्वावेनहिपितामहः सुराणामसुराणांचधर्माधर्मौतदाश्रयौ ।","trans":"\"The divine Brahma, the grandfather of the universe created two orders, deities and devils. They took the refuge of virtues and vices respectively.\"","words":[{"d":"भगवान्","m":"God"},{"d":"पितामहः","m":"grandfather Brahma"},{"d":"सुराणांच","m":"deities and"},{"d":"असुराणांच","m":"devils also"},{"d":"द्वौ","m":"both"},{"d":"पक्षौएव","m":"orders"},{"d":"असृजत्","m":"created beings"},{"d":"धर्माधर्मौ","m":"virtue and vice"},{"d":"तदाश्रयौ","m":"taking refuge."}]},{"v":13,"dev":"धर्मोहिश्रूयतेपक्षीह्यमराणांमहात्मनाम् अधर्मोरक्षसांपक्षोह्यसुराणांचराक्षस ।","trans":"\"The great souls were towards righteousness and Rakshasas took the side of unrighteousness.\"","words":[{"d":"राक्षस","m":"Rakshasa"},{"d":"धर्मः","m":"righteous"},{"d":"महात्मानाम्","m":"great souls"},{"d":"असुराणाम्","m":"and Rakshasas"},{"d":"पक्षी","m":"side"},{"d":"अधर्मः","m":"unrighteous"},{"d":"रक्षसाम्","m":"Rakshasas"},{"d":"असुराणांच","m":"and devils"},{"d":"पक्षःहि","m":"being the side."}]},{"v":14,"dev":"धर्मोवैग्रसतेऽधर्मंततःकृतमभूद्युगम् अधर्मोग्रसतेधर्मंततस्तिष्यःप्रवर्तते ।","trans":"\"When moral merit destroys unrighteousness, it is called Krtayuga. So also, when virtue gets eclipsed by unrighteousness, it is called Kaliyuga.\"","words":[{"d":"धर्मः","m":"moral merit"},{"d":"यदा","m":"similarly"},{"d":"अधर्मम्","m":"unrighteous"},{"d":"ग्रसते","m":"destroyed"},{"d":"कृतंयुगम्","m":"Krtam Yuga"},{"d":"अभूत्","m":"not exist"},{"d":"अधर्मः","m":"unrighteousness"},{"d":"धर्मम्","m":"righteousness"},{"d":"ग्रसते","m":"eclipses"},{"d":"तदा","m":"so also"},{"d":"तिष्यः","m":"end"},{"d":"प्रवर्तते","m":"commences."}]},{"v":15,"dev":"तत्त्वयाचरयालोकान्धर्मोपिविनिहतोमहान् अधर्मःप्रगृहीतश्चतेनास्मद्बलिनःपरे ।","trans":"\"While you were ranging in all the worlds, you gave up righteousness and embraced unrighteousness. Therefore, the enemy who is righteous is stronger than you.\"","words":[{"d":"सत्","m":"being good"},{"d":"लोकान्","m":"the worlds"},{"d":"चरता","m":"ranging"},{"d":"त्वया","m":"by you"},{"d":"महान्","m":"great"},{"d":"धर्मोऽपि","m":"even righteous conduct"},{"d":"विनिहतः","m":"giving up"},{"d":"अधर्मः","m":"unrighteous"},{"d":"प्रगृहीतश्च","m":"embraced by you"},{"d":"तेन","m":"therefore"},{"d":"परे","m":"enemy"},{"d":"अस्मत्","m":"more than you"},{"d":"बलिनः","m":"stronger."}]},{"v":16,"dev":"सप्रमादावदिवृद्धस्तेऽधर्मोहिग्रसतेहिनः विवर्थयतिपक्षंचसुराणांसुरभावनः ।","trans":"\"You are nourishing unrighteousness mistakenly. Therefore, it is going to swallow us. It has become the cause for the divine celestial side to become powerful.\"","words":[{"d":"ते","m":"you"},{"d":"प्रमदात्","m":"mistakenly"},{"d":"वदिवृद्धः","m":"nourishing"},{"d":"सः","m":"he"},{"d":"अधर्मः","m":"unrighteous"},{"d":"वः","m":"those"},{"d":"ग्रसतेहि","m":"will swallow"},{"d":"सुरभावनः","m":"cause of celestials (to become powerful)"},{"d":"सुराणाम्","m":"for the divine celestials"},{"d":"पक्षम्","m":"side"},{"d":"विवर्थयतिच","m":"grow in strength also."}]},{"v":17,"dev":"विषयेषुप्रसक्तेनयत्किञ्चित्कारणात्वया ऋषीणामग्नकल्पानामुद्वेगोजनितोमहान् ।","trans":"\"Being engaged in matters of sense pleasures you have created great agitation(disturbance) in the minds of the seers (engaged in penance) who resemble gods of burning fire.\"","words":[{"d":"विषयेषु","m":"in matters"},{"d":"प्रसक्तेन","m":"excessively engaged in"},{"d":"यत्किञ्चित्कारणा","m":"indeed for that reason"},{"d":"त्वया","m":"by you"},{"d":"अग्निकल्पनामा","m":"burning fire"},{"d":"ऋषीणाम्","m":"to the seers"},{"d":"महान्","m":"great"},{"d":"उद्वेगः","m":"agitation"},{"d":"जनितः","m":"created."}]},{"v":18,"dev":"तेषांप्रभावोदुर्धर्षःप्रदीप्तइवपावकः तपसाभावितात्मानोधर्मस्यानुग्रहेरताः ।मुख्यर्यज्ञैर्यजन्त्येतेनित्यंतैस्सैर्द्विजातयः जुह्वत्यनगींश्चविधिवद्वेदांश्चोच्चैरधीयते ।अभिभूयचरक्षांसिब्रह्मघोषानुदैरयन् दिशोऽपिविद्रुतास्सर्वेस्तनयित्नुरिवोष्णगे ।","trans":"\"Their power is difficult to overcome as they are pure souls and blazing like fire by their austerity. They follow virtues faithfully intending to acquire merit like brahmanas. They are standing firmly curbing their senses doing sacrifices offering oblations into sacrificial fires following tradition. Having subdued the Rakshasas, they are continuing to recite Vedas and on hearing Vedas the Rakshasas are running away in different directions like the rain cloud is scattered in the hot season.\"","words":[{"d":"तेषाम्","m":"their"},{"d":"प्रभावः","m":"power"},{"d":"प्रदीप्तः","m":"blazing"},{"d":"पावकःइव","m":"like fire"},{"d":"दुर्धर्षः","m":"difficult to overcome"},{"d":"तपसा","m":"austerity"},{"d":"भावितात्मानः","m":"greatpure souls"},{"d":"धर्मस्य","m":"virtues"},{"d":"अनुग्रहे","m":"following"},{"d":"रताः","m":"remaining"},{"d":"तेनित्यं","m":"all of them"},{"d":"द्विजातयः","m":"Brahmanas"},{"d":"मुख्यैः","m":"important"},{"d":"तैस्सैः","m":"standing firmly"},{"d":"यज्ञैः","m":"sacred fire"},{"d":"यत्","m":"curbing the senses"},{"d":"यजन्ति","m":"sacrificing"},{"d":"अनगींश्च","m":"into fire"},{"d":"जुह्वति","m":"offering oblations"},{"d":"विधिवत्","m":"traditionally"},{"d":"वेदान्","m":"Vedas"},{"d":"उच्चैः","m":"reciting"},{"d":"अधीयते","m":"chanting constantly"},{"d":"रक्षांसि","m":"Rakshasas"},{"d":"अभिभूय","m":"subdue"},{"d":"ब्रह्मघोषान्","m":"mistakes"},{"d":"उदैरयन्","m":"intending"},{"d":"सर्वे","m":"all"},{"d":"उष्णगे","m